eld. </p><p><b>steven a. grimm –</b> grimm is the wood county assessor. he lives in parkersburg. </p><p><b>priscilla haden –</b> haden lives in charleston, and is a civic leader in kanawha leader. </p><p><b>brian long –</b> long is the chair of the marshall county (PARTY NAME) party. he lives in glen dale. </p><p><b>jeffrey loudin –</b> loudin is a member, of the randolph county (PARTY NAME) executive committee. he lives in elkins. </p><p><b>jerry mays –</b> mays, of martinsburg, is the former chair of the berkeley county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><b>catherine "sue" mckinney –</b> mckinney, of bridgeport, is the chair of the harrison county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><b>thomas joseph o'neill –</b> o'neill, of morgantown, is the vice chairman of the west virginia (PARTY NAME) state executive committee. </p><p><b>bill phillips, jr. –</b> phillips, of elkins, was the chief of staff to former governor cecil h. underwood. </p><p><b>melody potter –</b> potter, who lives in charleston, is the chair of the kanawha county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><b>carolyn rader –</b> rader, of ripley, is chair of the jackson county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><b>marti riggall –</b> riggall, of charleston, is a member of kanawha county (PARTY NAME) women. </p><p><b>james shaffer –</b> shaffer, of morgantown, is a member of the west virginia (PARTY NAME) state committee. </p><p><b>christopher wakim –</b> wakim, of wheeling, was a 2006 congressional candidate and is a former member of the west virginia legislature.</p></span>



